node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Amy Groesbeck on July 19, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
SUNDAY SCRIBBLES coming at you on a Monday because not knowing what day it is this summer has reached a new level. 🤪 Volume 2 of my Bulletin Board Letters with AG Fonts is now available and features more of my favorite chunky fonts, including  AG Thirty-Something, AG On Fleek, AG The Mothership, and AG Will There Be Snacks. 
#agfonts #teachersofinstagram #iteachtoo #bulletinboards #teachersfollowteachers #classroomdecor 
bit.ly/AgFontBulletinBoardVol2

node.text: Last day of school memory scoot! I posted these questions around the room and the mini humans wrote their responses in a special colored marker. Then we gathered on the “imaginary rug” (the term we coined our nonexistent rug this year) and shared our responses. Making new friends and listening to Mrs. Groesbeck sing random, made-up-on-the-spot songs were our top two most memorable moments. #lastdayofschool #thirdistheword

node.text: Tis’ the season to pack and store all the things! How do you store your anchor charts? At the end of the year, I rarely throw away my charts. Instead, I roll them up by subject and store them in a large plastic storage bin so I can refer back to a chart when I’m ready to prep and remake it next year. #protip #classroomorganization #theamygroesbeckanchorchart
